frus:attachment.p:
The Commission shall decide the method of laying to be chosen among the means
                        hereafter enumerated: 

                                a)

By junction with natural objects;

                                b)

By geographical coordination (Latitude and longitude and
                                eventually altitude);

                                c)

By rectangular coordination (X and Y for a known
                                projection);

                                d)

By relation to neighboring landmarks;

                                e)

By simple reference to the map;

                                f)

By photographs taken in the known directions.

list.item:
The protocols established by the Commission for all the decisions
                            taken by common accord to complete or determine the terms of the
                            Treaty;
